summary: After A4, I want Rhodey and Carol to co-lead the Avengers so bad, bc they're the most best suited for the job. Having two...
body:
After A4, I want Rhodey and Carol to co-lead the Avengers so bad, bc they’re the most best suited for the job. Having two leaders will lessen the load of either of them and they will actually KNOW how to work together and lead together, because they’re both air force colonels and trained in the army. They’ll know a thing or two about field tactics and where to place who, etc.

That’s the reason the old Avengers never worked, bc there was never enough communication, there was hiding and lying, no unity whatsoever, they were hell bent on killing/ hurting each other the first chance they got, and worst of all, there was no system, or protocol, or just a basic certain way of doing stuff. Any enhanced person just rolled on in and were called an Avenger, and in the field they did whatever the fucking hell they wanted, no questions and consequences, for certain people that is. Far as I know, they never did any proper press either, it was just Tony answering to the paps. That was actually the real reason I was pro Accords.

I feel like Carol and Rhodey would do a great job of leading the new Avengers, and even under the Accords, (which if I’m not wrong are negotiable), they would get more wins than losses, because any threat that a country isn’t equipped to deal with, the Avengers could fly in, neutralize the threat and begone. And because they’ve signed the Accords, going in and coming out of a country in threat/emergency cases won’t be a problem.

James Rhodes and Carol Danvers are going to kick some fucking ass if they lead the Avengers and if the writers (🙄) let it happen.
